This Administrations’ policies of separating children & families and keeping them in detention centers w/ little access to basic necessities is needlessly cruel and wrong. The House will continue to work to hold this Administration accountable and end these inhumane policies. 2/2

Last night, I voted to pass legislation to set humanitarian standards for children & families at the border in a way that respects human rights and aligns with our country’s values. I urge the Senate to act now & get this bill to the President's desk. 1/2 https://bit.ly/30Ut5k9

The robocall epidemic is out of control - I've heard from so many Kansans who are sick of these unwanted and often fraudulent calls. 

That's why I voted to pass the #StopBadRobocalls Act to put an end to the onslaught of robocalls once and for all.

I was also proud to co-sponsor a bipartisan amendment to make sure we’re examining the impacts of the bill midway through implementation, so that Congress can get a clear understanding of its impact and take any needed action to ensure our workers and businesses can thrive. (2/2)

After more than a decade with no raise in the federal minimum wage – the longest period in U.S. history – I was proud to vote today for a phased-in increase to the federal minimum wage to help hard-working Kansans and their families. (1/2)

As the daughter of an Army Veteran, I've seen the challenges our service members face when transitioning to new jobs. I introduced the SERV Act to study the barriers Veteran-owned businesses face, like access to credit, so we can help them succeed.
